From: Ilya Dryomov <idryomov@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 3 Sep 2020 13:24:11 +0200
Subject: rbd: require global CAP_SYS_ADMIN for mapping and unmapping
Git-commit: f44d04e696feaf13d192d942c4f14ad2e117065a
Patch-mainline: v5.9-rc5
References: CVE-2020-25284 bsc#1176482

It turns out that currently we rely only on sysfs attribute
permissions:

  $ ll /sys/bus/rbd/{add*,remove*}
  --w------- 1 root root 4096 Sep  3 20:37 /sys/bus/rbd/add
  --w------- 1 root root 4096 Sep  3 20:37 /sys/bus/rbd/add_single_major
  --w------- 1 root root 4096 Sep  3 20:37 /sys/bus/rbd/remove
  --w------- 1 root root 4096 Sep  3 20:38 /sys/bus/rbd/remove_single_major

This means that images can be mapped and unmapped (i.e. block devices
can be created and deleted) by a UID 0 process even after it drops all
privileges or by any process with CAP_DAC_OVERRIDE in its user namespace
as long as UID 0 is mapped into that user namespace.

Be consistent with other virtual block devices (loop, nbd, dm, md, etc)
and require CAP_SYS_ADMIN in the initial user namespace for mapping and
unmapping, and also for dumping the configuration string and refreshing
the image header.

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Ilya Dryomov <idryomov@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Jeff Layton <jlayton@kernel.org>
[luis: dropped hunk #1 as we don't have commit 0d6d1e9c2e97 ("rbd: add
'config_info' sysfs rbd device attribute")]
Acked-by: Luis Henriques <lhenriques@suse.com>
---
 drivers/block/rbd.c |    9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/block/rbd.c
+++ b/drivers/block/rbd.c
@@ -3635,6 +3635,9 @@ static ssize_t rbd_image_refresh(struct
 	struct rbd_device *rbd_dev = dev_to_rbd_dev(dev);
 	int ret;
 
+	if (!capable(CAP_SYS_ADMIN))
+		return -EPERM;
+
 	ret = rbd_dev_refresh(rbd_dev);
 	if (ret)
 		rbd_warn(rbd_dev, ": manual header refresh error (%d)\n", ret);
@@ -5074,6 +5077,9 @@ static ssize_t do_rbd_add(struct bus_typ
 	bool read_only;
 	int rc = -ENOMEM;
 
+	if (!capable(CAP_SYS_ADMIN))
+		return -EPERM;
+
 	if (!try_module_get(THIS_MODULE))
 		return -ENODEV;
 
@@ -5218,6 +5224,9 @@ static ssize_t do_rbd_remove(struct bus_
 	bool already = false;
 	int ret;
 
+	if (!capable(CAP_SYS_ADMIN))
+		return -EPERM;
+
 	ret = kstrtoul(buf, 10, &ul);
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
